  <prompt>
    Add a persona dropdown to the Playbook properties form in PlaybookBuilder so that
    makers can attach a CUST- or playbook-bound `sprk_aipersona` to a playbook.

    Without this UI, only the SYS-DEFAULT persona resolution layer is reachable — the
    CUST- and playbook-attached layers exist in `AnalysisPersonaService` code but are
    unauthored.

    **Source of truth**: `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/r6-deliverables-audit.md`
    section "Pillar 1 — Persona" identifies this as Phase 3a, ~1 day effort.

    **Backend already shipped** (tasks 001-005 ✅):
    - `sprk_aipersona` entity exists
    - `GET /api/ai/scopes/personas` endpoint returns available personas
    - `AnalysisPersonaService.GetEffectivePersonaAsync` does most-specific-wins resolution
    - `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` consumes the effective persona

    **UI work scope**:
    1. Add persona lookup field to playbook properties form in PlaybookBuilder code-page
    2. Wire lookup to `/api/ai/scopes/personas` for type-ahead
    3. Save selected persona ID on `sprk_analysisplaybook.sprk_personaid` (verify field exists or add via dataverse-create-schema)
    4. Display effective persona in playbook header (read-only "Effective: SYS-DEFAULT" or selected)
    5. UAT: create a CUST- persona row in Dataverse, attach to a playbook, run /summarize, verify system prompt reflects the attached persona

    **Out of scope**: per-session persona override in chat session UI (R7).
  </prompt>
</task>
